It is because `AbstractTestExecutionListener` is not a Spring Bean. So if you expect to be injected by field injection, it wouldn&#39;t work.

But you can extract a port from the `TestContext` which is injected in the method.

`@Value(&quot;${local.server.port}&quot;)` is exactly the same with `@LocalServerPort`.

```java
@Override
public void afterTestMethod(final TestContext testContext) throws Exception {
	Environment environment = testContext.getApplicationContext().getEnvironment();
	int port = environment.getProperty(&quot;local.server.port&quot;, Integer.class);
	RestAssured.port = port;
	JdbcTemplate jdbcTemplate = testContext.getApplicationContext().getBean(JdbcTemplate.class);

	List&lt;String&gt; truncateAllTablesQuery = jdbcTemplate.queryForList(&quot;SELECT CONCAT(&#39;TRUNCATE TABLE &#39;, TABLE_NAME, &#39;;&#39;) AS q FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES WHERE TABLE_SCHEMA = &#39;chatUniv&#39;&quot;, String.class);
	truncateAllTables(jdbcTemplate, truncateAllTablesQuery);
}
```

